cs.IT, cs.COMM, cs.SI, cs.NI, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
1. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper proposes a practical polar coded modulation scheme and discusses the optimal labeling rule for the constellation. This falls under the domain of information theory.
2. cs.COMM (Communications and Networking) - The proposed scheme is compared with the bit-interleaved turbo coded modulation scheme used in WCDMA mobile communication systems. This indicates that the paper is related to communication systems.
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper deals with the design of a modulation scheme and optimal labeling rule, which involves signal processing techniques.
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper discusses the performance of the proposed scheme in a mobile communication system, which falls under the domain of networking and internet architecture.
5. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) - The paper discusses the search space reduction technique used to efficiently find the optimal labeling rule, which involves algorithmic techniques.
